item.title: Das Cube 2 (sticker template)
item.description:
Download the files for this puzzle from Oskar van Deventer's website: http://oskarvandeventer.nl/Print-It-Yourself/

I am posting a sticker template I made for the Das Cube 2, because the template Oskar provided did not import correctly into Silhouette Studio for me.

It's a mix and match template; for each face, just cut the amount of stickers you need of each type. The center sticker is not identical to the stickers for the large cubies, so don't confuse them.

I have made a video about this puzzle including the build, a demonstration, scramble, and solve: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=KMUT6qJCSe4

item.title: Raspberry 3 B+ Case Voronoi Style with Pi-Cam
item.description:
Noch ein Raspberry case... als gäbe es nicht schon genug.

Ich habe mir ein Case für meinen Raspberry Pi 3 B+ erstellt, welches ich in den vslot einhängen kann, ja, nur in waagerechte Profile einhängen.
Die allgemeine Idee mit dem Kameraausleger habe ich aus dem Design von ksamuelsen.

Für den Zusammenbau werden noch folgende Teile benötigt:
8x Einschmelzgewinde M3
https://www.amazon.de/ruthex-Gewindeeinsatz-St%C3%BCck-Gewindebuchsen-Kunststoffteile/dp/B08BCRZZS3/ref=sr_1_5?__mk_de_DE=%C3%85M%C3%85%C5%BD%C3%95%C3%91&crid=1C8HJDJTR93HL&keywords=rutex&qid=1643374946&sprefix=rutex%2Caps%2C84&sr=8-5&th=1
4x M3x6 z.B. (ich habe etwas längere verwendet und auf dem Pi noch Kunststoffscheiben drauf.)
4x M3x18 Zylinderkopf

Und beim Verwenden der Camera noch
3x M3 Muttern
3x M3x10

Die 4 Löcher im Pi müssen noch auf 3 bis 3,3 mm aufgebohrt werden. Macht aber keine Probleme.

Das Kameragehäuse wird nur gepresst, hält aber gut.

Gedruckt wurde alles mit
Layer high 0,2
Infill 20%
Kein Brimm
Support
Case oben (Flache Seite nach unten, Support für die Schraubenlöcher)
Arm kurz 90Grad
Arm lang
Camera Case Halter (hochkant drucken und Aufmalstützen an dem Überhang anbringen.)

Wer noch möchte kann mir gerne eine Kleinigkeit für ne Tasse Kaffee zukommen lassen.

https://paypal.me/julsch74?country.x=DE&locale.x=de_DE

Another Raspberry case... as if there were not already enough.

I created a case for my Raspberry Pi 3 B+ that I can hook into the vslot, yes, only hook into horizontal profiles.
I got the general idea with the camera boom from ksamuelsen's design.

For the assembly the following parts are still needed:
8x M3 fusible thread
https://www.amazon.de/ruthex-Gewindeeinsatz-St%C3%BCck-Gewindebuchsen-Kunststoffteile/dp/B08BCRZZS3/ref=sr_1_5?__mk_de_DE=%C3%85M%C3%85%C5%BD%C3%95%C3%91&crid=1C8HJDJTR93HL&keywords=rutex&qid=1643374946&sprefix=rutex%2Caps%2C84&sr=8-5&th=1

4x M3x6 e.g. (I used a bit longer and put plastic washers on the Pi).
4x M3x18 cylinder head

And when using the Camera still
3x M3 nuts
3x M3x10

The 4 holes in the Pi still have to be drilled out to 3 to 3.3 mm. But this does not cause any problems.

The camera housing is only pressed, but holds well.

Printed everything with
Layer high 0.2
Infill 20%
No Brim
Support
Case top (flat side down, support for screw holes)
Arm short 90deg
Arm long
Camera Case Holder (Print on edge and attach paint-on supports to the overhang.)

Who still wants can send me a little something for a cup of coffee.
https://paypal.me/julsch74?country.x=DE&locale.x=de_DE

item.title: Gem Generator
item.description:
Generate cartoon-styled gemstones with our latest, free, 3D printable design.

This simple customizable design allows you to choose the number of sides, dimensions and proportions of your gemstones.

This design is completely free and shared under a permissive license. Your support is hugely appreciated.

Did you know?

Some of our designs cannot be found on Thingiverse. If you are looking for more, check out our premium projects:

https://codeandmake.com/premium

OpenSCAD Customizer Options

We recommend you use OpenSCAD to customize this design.

This design has the following Customizer options:

  • Diameter - Diameter at widest point
  • Sides - Number of sides
  • Bottom_Height - Uncut height of bottom section
  • Bottom_Cutoff_Percent - Percentage to cut from bottom section
  • Top_Height - Uncut height of top section
  • Top_Cutoff_Percent - Percentage to cut from top section
  • Orientation - Rotate onto side or top for easier printing

Design Considerations

In many cases, it should be possible to print designs without supports. For the best results, consider the angle of overhangs and use the Orientation option.

Material

This design is perfect for printing in most filaments, but we recommend translucent filaments/resins in particular for this design.

Versions

  • 1.0 (28 Jan 2021) - Initial version

Printing

Recommended slicer settings:

  • Resolution: 0.1mm - 0.2mm
  • Infill: ~10 - 20% recommended.
  • Supports: Should not be required for most designs, but designs with significant overhangs will require supports.
  • Rafts: Not required, unless you experience adhesion issues.

License

The "Gem Generator" models (.stl) are licensed under the CC BY license by Code and Make.

The "Gem Generator" code (.scad) is licensed under The MIT License by Code and Make.

Note: 'BSD' license has been selected as it is the closest available option in the list.

We are proud to offer content to you absolutely free.

We love to create free content for you. As you might imagine, it takes a lot of time. Supporters help us fund materials and equipment to create future projects and tutorials. To show your appreciation, please use the link below:

https://codeandmake.com/support

We thank you so much for your support!

item.title: Nissan Laurel C35 for 1/10 Chassis
item.description:
I had recently printed the Chasis 1/10 Adaptable by dukedoks and wanted to print a shell for it. I came across ninjarixx's Nissan Laurel C35 and figured I'd try and make it work. The body was scaled to adjust tire fitment and then I added locations for the magnets to be mounted underneath the shell. The shell was then split up into 3 separate pieces for ease of printing. I then had to modify the front bumper for the Chasis 1/10 Adaptable for the Shell to fit over it. I have included the 3 shell pieces and the modified front bumper.

To assemble the C35 Shell I used 14 x M3x8mm screws and 14 x M3 nuts. I then used the same magnets that dukedoks used on the chassis.

item.title: Sd.Kfz. 234 Puma Schwebelafette
item.description:
Sd.Kfz. 234 Puma Schwebelafette is a very special version of the Puma Armoured Car.

Based on a Stummel version hull, it had a Sd.Kfz. 251/17 AA gun. It was a field conversion made in 1945 from a german unito in Czechoslovakia.

There are only few photos about it, and a video showing surrendered german troops retreatinz from Czech territory.

( I USED THE GUN OF A HALFTRACK MADE BY TIGERACE ! )

item.title: Wire guide fpv frame
item.description:
This is a clip for wires so your fpv setup looks more clean.
It was designed for the tbs source one v3 frame which has a leg of 4x16mm.
It might fit on other frames too you just have to measure the leg thickness.

The weight is approx 1 gram per leg so it won't affect your flying.
